main event: Two witnesses in Bethel, Vermont observed two unidentified flying objects in the sky on January 8, 1965.
interesting points: The first object was described as round, reddish-orange in color, and pulsating.
The second object was similar in appearance, also round, reddish-orange, and pulsating.
The objects were in view for approximately 10-15 minutes before disappearing from sight.
There were no sound effects associated with the objects.
The witnesses stated the objects appeared to be metallic in nature and were definitely not aircraft, satellites, or any other known type of aerial vehicle.
